		<p>
			The purpose of Renter is to document the condition of your apartment at the start of a lease-period and have a verifiable way for your landlord to acknowledge its condition as well. It's simple and practical. It's not a sexy idea. It's the kind of practical advice that overprotective fathers tell their daughters before they move in to their first apartment. Which is exactly where the idea is from. Except, in my case, my father told me that I should print the photos and then mail them to my landlord via certified mail. Good advice, but it's 2014, and if there's one thing I dislike doing, it's going to the post office. Surely, there could be a better way. <br>Thus, Renter was born.
